@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Workstation — Medicare";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

@section Styles {
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/scripts-rebuttals.css" asp-append-version="true" />
}


<div id="mpShell">
    <div class="mp-shell">
        <aside class="mp-side">
            <div class="side-card">
                <div class="side-head">
                    <p class="side-title">Elite Call Guide</p>
                    <p class="side-sub">Follow the path. Control the call. Close clean.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="side-tools">
                    <input id="mpSearch" class="side-search" placeholder="Search + highlight… (doctors, prescriptions, Medicare, voicemail)" />

                    <div class="side-actions">
                        <button class="btn gold" type="button" id="btnNext">Next Step</button>
                        <button class="btn" type="button" id="btnExpand">Expand All</button>
                        <button class="btn" type="button" id="btnCollapse">Collapse All</button>
                        <button class="btn dark" type="button" id="btnClear">Clear Search</button>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="side-progress">
                    <div class="prog-row">
                        <div class="prog-label">Progress</div>
                        <div class="prog-pill"><span id="progDone">0</span>/<span id="progTotal">0</span></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="prog-bar"><div class="prog-fill" id="progFill"></div></div>
                </div>

                <nav class="side-nav" id="sideNav" aria-label="Script steps"></nav>
            </div>
        </aside>

        <main class="mp-main">
            <div class="mp-hero">
                <div class="mp-hero-top">
                    <div>
                        <h1>Workstation — Medicare</h1>
                        <p>Zero guessing. This page guides the agent from contact → verify → review → enroll → close out.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="top-row">
                    <span class="pill"><span class="dot good"></span> Proceed / next</span>
                    <span class="pill"><span class="dot warn"></span> Clarify / slow down</span>
                    <span class="pill"><span class="dot bad"></span> Objection / unsure</span>
                </div>

                <div class="script-legend">
                    <span class="legend-chip say"><span class="swatch"></span> Say this</span>
                    <span class="legend-chip fill"><span class="swatch"></span> Fill this in</span>
                    <span class="legend-chip silent"><span class="swatch"></span> Do NOT read this out loud</span>
                    <span class="legend-chip note"><span class="swatch"></span> Agent direction</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="focus-banner" id="focusBanner">
                <div class="left">
                    <div class="t1">Focus Mode is ON</div>
                    <div class="t2">You’re viewing one step only. Keep the call clean.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="right">
                    <button class="btn-ghost" type="button" id="btnExitFocus">Exit Focus</button>
                    <button class="btn-ghost" type="button" id="btnNextFocus">Next Step</button>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card" id="mpCard">

                <details class="section" data-step="0" data-flow="verify" data-signal="bad" id="sec-hub">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">⚠️ Unsure / Objection Hub</span>
                                <span class="sub">Stop. Clarify. Then route.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-back>Back</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout bad">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue bad">STOP</span> Don’t push. Clarify the obstacle.
                                <div class="hint">Ask one clean question that forces truth.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="hubStop" class="script"><span class="say">Totally fair — quick question so I don’t waste your time:
Is it the doctors, the prescriptions, the cost, or are you just unsure what this even is?</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="keyline"><strong>ROUTE BUTTONS</strong> (tap to jump)</div>
                        <div class="side-actions" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
                            <button class="btn" type="button" data-jump="#sec-threeins">“What is this?”</button>
                            <button class="btn" type="button" data-jump="#sec-equity">Need meaning / emotion</button>
                            <button class="btn" type="button" data-jump="#sec-options-choose">Choosing options</button>
                            <button class="btn dark" type="button" data-jump="#sec-closeout">Close out / tie-down</button>
                        </div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="callout warn">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue warn">RULE</span> After you answer, ask for a micro-yes.
                                <div class="hint">“That make sense?” then move immediately to the next step.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="1" data-flow="start" data-signal="good" id="sec-voicemail">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Voicemail Script</span>
                                <span class="sub">Authority + urgency. No rambling.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-voicemail">Focus</button>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Unsure?</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout good">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue good">GO</span> Drop the message like you’re correcting paperwork.
                                <div class="hint">Goal: callback. Not a conversation.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="vm" class="script"><span class="say">This message is for </span><span class="fill">&lt;CLIENT NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, this is </span><span class="fill">&lt;YOUR NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">. I manage the brokerage that handles Medicare plan reviews for families in your area. We do have pending paperwork to get back to you regarding the Medicare review you requested. Give me a call back at </span><span class="fill">&lt;YOUR PHONE NUMBER&gt;</span><span class="say">. Talk to you soon.</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="callout warn">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue warn">STOP</span> If they call back angry: don’t explain yet.
                                <div class="hint">First line: “Totally fair — let me pull up your file.” Then verify identity.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="side-actions" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
                            <button class="btn" type="button" data-jump="#sec-aged">Go to Aged Lead Opener</button>
                            <button class="btn dark" type="button" data-jump="#sec-verify">Verify Current Coverage Lane</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="2" data-flow="start" data-signal="warn" id="sec-texts">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Text Scripts</span>
                                <span class="sub">Direction only. No debate.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-texts">Focus</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>

                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout warn">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue warn">RULE</span> If they respond with questions → move to call.
                                <div class="hint">Text ends with “What time today works?”</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="keyline"><strong>TEXT (1)</strong> Quick “pending paperwork” text.</div>
                        <div id="txt1" class="script"><span class="fill">&lt;NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, this is </span><span class="fill">&lt;YOUR NAME&gt;</span><span class="say"> regarding the Medicare review request we received. Give me a call back when you get this, we have some pending paperwork to get out to you regarding your Medicare coverage review. The office number is </span><span class="fill">&lt;OFFICE NUMBER&gt;</span><span class="say">. Thanks.</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="keyline"><strong>TEXT (2)</strong> Underwriter assigned + book a call.</div>
                        <div id="txt2" class="script"><span class="fill">&lt;NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, it’s </span><span class="fill">&lt;YOUR NAME&gt;</span><span class="say"> following up with you on the request you filled out and mailed in to us regarding your Medicare review. This is the review that helps make sure your doctors, prescriptions, and out-of-pocket costs are lined up correctly.

I'm the field underwriter assigned to help you take care of this for your family. What time are you available for me to give you a call today or tomorrow?</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="keyline"><strong>APPT CONFIRM</strong> Set expectation + get acknowledgement.</div>
                        <div id="txtConfirm" class="script"><span class="say">Hey </span><span class="fill">&lt;NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, </span><span class="fill">&lt;YOUR NAME&gt;</span><span class="say"> here, medical underwriter. Confirming our appointment at </span><span class="fill">&lt;TIME&gt;</span><span class="say">. If there is any reason you can’t make that meeting, please let myself or my staff know so we can reschedule and help another family in your place. I look forward to serving you and your family!

Reply “Yes” or give me a “👍🏻” to let me know you received this message.</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="keyline"><strong>HAIL MARY</strong> Reschedule + last attempt language.</div>
                        <div id="txtHail" class="script"><span class="say">Hey, just gave a call for our appointment. Do you need a few minutes?

Just need to get this rescheduled — will later today or tomorrow work better for you?
I have some availability this evening. If not, I can try to squeeze you in for tomorrow. I know this is important to you. Give me a call back when you get this.

Tried to reach out a few times and haven't heard back…
Where should we go from here?</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="callout bad">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue bad">STOP</span> If they reply “What is this?” → don’t type a paragraph.
                                <div class="hint">Jump to the Medicare explanation and bring them to a call.</div>
                            </div>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-threeins">Go to “What Medicare Review Is”</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" open data-step="3" data-flow="verify" data-signal="good" id="sec-aged">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Mail-In Aged Leads</span>
                                <span class="sub">Purple chill / Red concerned.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-aged">Focus</button>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Unsure?</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>

                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout good">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue good">PURPLE</span> Chill tone
                                <span class="cue bad">RED</span> Concerned / confused tone
                                <div class="hint">Goal: “file correction” not “sales pitch”.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="agedOpen" class="script"><span class="say">Yeah, </span><span class="fill">&lt;CLIENT&gt;</span><span class="say">? This is </span><span class="fill">&lt;YOUR NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">. Had to give you a quick call here... I manage the brokerage that handles Medicare plan reviews for families in your area.</span>
Your file came across my desk… still showing me as incomplete… you probably remember… sometime back you requested information and we sent you several documents in the mail about your Medicare coverage review. Right… where we make sure your doctors, prescriptions, and benefits are in the most comfortable fit. Do you remember that?

It looks like you actually did the right thing. You filled out the form and mailed it back to us, but for whatever reason on our end, we still haven't got that completed. I'm the senior underwriter, so it’s my job to see what’s going on so we can get this taken care of. By chance, do you remember one of our junior underwriters reaching out to take care of you?</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="callout bad">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue bad">STOP</span> If they say “Yeah I already have something” → verify, don’t accept.
                                <div class="hint">Route: “Figure Out What They Have”.</div>
                            </div>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-verify">Go Verify Lane</button>
                        </div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="callout warn">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue warn">IF IMMEDIATE YES</span> Clarify and confirm the process.
                                <div class="hint">Goal: catch lies gently and route correctly.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="clarify" class="script"><span class="say">So it is </span><span class="fill">&lt;STATE&gt;</span><span class="say"> state law that once you enroll, you would have received plan documents and carrier paperwork in the mail — I’m assuming you received that, right? Okay, now you also would have reviewed your doctors, prescriptions, and benefits with one of our underwriters before getting enrolled. I’m assuming you did that too, right?</span></div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="4" data-flow="verify" data-signal="bad" id="sec-verify">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Figure Out What They Have</span>
                                <span class="sub">People lie — verify fast.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-verify">Focus</button>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Unsure?</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>

                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout bad">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue bad">STOP</span> Do NOT go “options” yet.
                                <div class="hint">You must establish the lane: Current plan review vs fresh enrollment.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="keyline"><strong>IF HAVE COVERAGE</strong> Update file → review path.</div>
                        <div id="haveCoverage" class="script"><span class="say">Okay, perfect. It looks like one of our junior underwriters was able to help you out, but for some reason they did not update your file here. Just so I can update the plan on my end, what did you get set up with?</span>
<span class="silent">GO INTO PLAN REVIEW</span></div>

                        <div style="height:10px"></div>
                        <button class="btn gold" type="button" data-jump="#sec-replace">➡️ Jump to Plan Review</button>

                        <div style="height:16px"></div>

                        <div class="keyline"><strong>IF NO COVERAGE</strong> Reframe → why they asked → start review.</div>
                        <div id="noCoverage" class="script"><span class="say">Okay, perfect — that’s probably why your file is flagged here. It looks like our junior medical underwriter wasn’t able to get ahold of you.

Now </span><span class="fill">&lt;CLIENT NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, correct me if I’m wrong… I’m assuming when you filled out the form you were looking for help making sure your doctors, prescriptions, and overall Medicare coverage were lined up correctly so you weren’t overpaying or getting caught in the wrong plan... does that sound about right?

Okay, and what were you mainly hoping to get help with — doctors, prescriptions, lower costs, or just making sure everything is set up right?...

If yes: Okay perfect, I’m the senior underwriter, like I said, and it’s my job to ask a couple questions to see what plan options may make the most sense for you.</span>
<span class="silent">START GATHERING DOCTORS, PRESCRIPTIONS, ZIP, COUNTY, CURRENT COVERAGE</span>
<span class="silent">GO INTO ONE CALL CLOSE SCRIPT</span></div>

                        <div style="height:10px"></div>
                        <button class="btn gold" type="button" data-jump="#sec-occ">➡️ Jump to One Call Close</button>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="5" data-flow="verify" data-signal="warn" id="sec-replace">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Plan Review</span>
                                <span class="sub">Annual review → better fit → better value.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-replace">Focus</button>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Unsure?</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>

                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout warn">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue warn">RULE</span> Never say “switch” first. Say “review”.
                                <div class="hint">You’re the fixer. Not the seller.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="callout bad">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue bad">STOP</span> If they get defensive → ask why they picked that plan.
                                <div class="hint">Then route into “options that match your real goal”.</div>
                            </div>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-options-choose">Go to Options Choice</button>
                        </div>

                        <div id="prKnown" class="script"><span class="note">If client knows carrier:</span>
<span class="silent">ACT CONFUSED</span>
<span class="say">Okay </span><span class="fill">&lt;NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, was there a certain reason they put you with that carrier? Are all of your doctors in network there and are your prescriptions coming through the way they should? I’m just a little confused here since </span><span class="fill">&lt;CARRIER NAME&gt;</span><span class="say"> is not always the most comfortable fit depending on what someone is taking and who they see.</span>
<span class="silent">GO TO REVIEW</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div id="prUnknown" class="script"><span class="note">If client doesn’t know carrier:</span>
<span class="say">Okay, did you get your plan documents or card in the mail? Okay, perfect.</span>
<span class="silent">GO TO REVIEW</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div id="prReplace" class="script"><span class="say">So </span><span class="fill">&lt;NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, it looks like your file was flagged for annual review. What that means is there have been some recent changes in the Medicare market in the state of </span><span class="fill">&lt;STATE&gt;</span><span class="say"> where folks who enrolled in the past are sometimes able to get into a more comfortable situation with their doctors, prescriptions, and out-of-pocket costs than what they currently have.

Now obviously </span><span class="fill">&lt;CLIENT&gt;</span><span class="say">, I know that is important to you, and every other family in the state of </span><span class="fill">&lt;STATE&gt;</span><span class="say">.

Now, what my job is today is to take a look at the plan you currently have and make sure that you are in the most comfortable and affordable situation currently, given those changes, in addition to making sure your doctors and prescriptions are lining up the way they should. Does that make sense?</span>

<span class="note">If they don’t have the plan info:</span>
<span class="say">Do you have your Medicare card or current plan card nearby? Because the company name should be on there.</span>

<span class="note">Once name found:</span>
<span class="say">Okay, and do you know which prescriptions you’re currently taking and which doctors you want to keep?</span>

<span class="silent">IF CANNOT FIND IT, PULL CURRENT COVERAGE WITH THEM OR VERIFY PLAN FROM CARD</span>
<span class="silent">IF THEY HAVE IT, GET DOCTORS / RX / COUNTY / ZIP AND FIND BETTER FIT</span></div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="6" data-flow="start" data-signal="warn" id="sec-book">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Booking the Appointment</span>
                                <span class="sub">Two times. Require spouse if involved.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-book">Focus</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout warn">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue warn">RULE</span> Don’t ask “what works?” — give two options.
                                <div class="hint">Control the calendar = control the close.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="book" class="script"><span class="say">Perfect, I typically do run appointments only anyway.

If they have a spouse helping with decisions:
Okay, we’ll want to make sure your spouse is on the call with us as well so we can go through the doctors, prescriptions, and plan options one time the right way. Do you both typically have availability during the day, or are evenings better? What does that look like for you?

They have me seeing about 10–12 families a day, let me look to see where we can squeeze you in.

Would sometime later today or tomorrow be better for you?
If tomorrow, is morning, afternoon, or evening best for you?</span>
<span class="silent">FINALIZE TIME</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <div class="callout bad">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue bad">STOP</span> If they avoid committing: don’t negotiate.
                                <div class="hint">Route to Hub and clarify the real objection.</div>
                            </div>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Go to Objection Hub</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="section" data-step="7" data-flow="close" data-signal="good" id="sec-occ">
                    <summary>
                        <div class="sum-left">
                            <div class="chev">›</div>
                            <div>
                                <span class="title">Start One Call Close</span>
                                <span class="sub">Frame → doctors → prescriptions → options.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sum-actions">
                            <button class="btn-mini good" type="button" data-focus="#sec-occ">Focus</button>
                            <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-jump="#sec-hub">Unsure?</button>
                        </div>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="body">
                        <div class="callout good">
                            <div>
                                <span class="cue good">GO</span> Calm certainty. This is process, not pitch.
                                <div class="hint">Get permission + set honesty expectation.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="occ" class="script"><span class="say">Okay great, is this your first time going through the Medicare review process?

Gotcha, and I am recording this call for quality assurance and training purposes. That’s okay with you?

Perfect, and just so you understand everything, I’ll explain the entire process.

It’s really simple. Again, I am an underwriter for an insurance brokerage, so it’s my job first to understand what you currently have, and next make sure your doctors, prescriptions, and benefits are lined up in the best possible way with one of the carriers we work with.

So I’m going to spend a couple minutes asking you some basic questions about your doctors, your prescriptions, and the type of Medicare coverage you have now so I can understand what plan options may make the most sense for you. So as I go through this and ask what doctors you see or what medications you take, just be honest with me so I can make sure we line this up the right way.

Next, I’ll ask a few basic questions about what matters most to you — whether that’s keeping certain doctors, lowering prescription costs, or making sure your overall out-of-pocket is more comfortable.

Does that make sense?

Based on that information, it’s my job as the medical underwriter to run it through the carriers in the state of </span><span class="fill">&lt;STATE&gt;</span><span class="say"> that offer Medicare plans in your area.

I’ll present those various options to you. After we decide what option is the most comfortable and practical, I basically become the paperwork guy, helping you submit the request for enrollment to the insurance carrier to make sure we can get everything handled correctly.

</span><span class="fill">&lt;NAME&gt;</span><span class="say">, what are we mainly trying to fix here today — doctors, prescriptions, lower costs, or just making sure everything is set up right?</span>

<span class="note">If spouse is involved in care decisions:</span>
<span class="say">And are we reviewing just your Medicare today, or are we looking at both of you to make sure everything is lined up correctly?</span></div>

                        <div style="height:12px"></div>

                        <details class="section" data-step="7A" data-flow="verify" data-signal="warn" id="sec-threeins">
                            <summary>
                                <div class="sum-left">
                                    <div class="chev">›</div>
                                    <div>
                                        <span class="title">What a Medicare Review Is (Client Unsure)</span>
                                        <span class="sub">20 seconds. Then move.</span>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="sum-actions">
                                    <button class="btn-mini bad" type="button" data-back>Back</button>
                                    <button class="btn-mini gold" type="button" data-jump="#sec-options-choose">Go Options</button>
                                </div>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="body">
                                <div class="callout warn">
                                    <div>
                                        <span class="cue warn">IF CLIENT IS UNSURE</span> Answer + immediately route forward.
                                        <div class="hint">Do not lecture. Do not ramble. “Make sense?” then review.</div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div id="threeIns" class="script"><span class="say">Now, the first part of my job is helping families get the right Medicare coverage, but secondly is education. Okay?

So </span><span class="fill">&lt;CLIENT&gt;</span><span class="say">, when it comes to Medicare, there are really a few moving parts people get confused by:

1. Original Medicare — that’s your Part A and Part B through the government.
2. Prescription coverage and plan structure — that’s where people can get caught with formularies, networks, deductibles, and co-pays if nobody actually reviews it right.
